decision_details:
- in December 2010 Cabinet has approved a proposal to draft a Bill to amend the Finance Act No.78 of 1988 with a view to providing for a strong governance framework to regulate finance business.  The purpose of this effort is to update the law with the developments in technology in keeping with international best practices to combat unauthorized deposit taking businesses and to ensure the stability of the financial sector.  Some of the salient features of the Bill are - 

		*	acceptance of deposits without authority is made an offence;
		*	definition of "deposit" is introduced; 
		*	enhanced examination/investigative powers;
		*	enhancement of supervisory action on licensed finance companies;
		*	enhanced public disclosure;
		*	enhanced penalties.

	The proposal made by H.E. the President to present the  relevant Bill in Parliament for approval, was approved by the Cabinet.
